  "copy": {
    "caption": "The water dragon that never quite grows up.",
    "shortDescription": "Axolotls keep their feathery pink gills on the outside of their heads for their whole lives, waving gently in the water like tiny fluttering fans. Most amphibians go through a tadpole stage and then transform into adults, but axolotls stay in their larval form forever — in the wild they only live in one lake in Mexico. Fun fact: An axolotl can regrow a lost limb, gill, eye, and even chunks of its own heart and brain."
